│ The `threadBinOpOverSelect` function is responsible for      │
│ simplifying binary operations involving `select`             │
│ instructions. It evaluates the binary operation on the true  │
│ and false branches of the `select` and attempts to simplify  │
│ the result. This function is relevant to the bug because the │
│ issue involves a `select` instruction producing a divisor    │
│ that can be zero in some lanes, leading to incorrect         │
│ simplifications.                                             │
│                                                              │
│ To fix the bug, we need to ensure that the                   │
│ `simplifyUDivInst` function properly handles cases where the │
│ divisor is derived from a `select` instruction.              │
│ Specifically, we need to verify that the divisor is non-zero │
│ for all lanes before applying the transformation. If the     │
│ divisor can be zero in any lane, the transformation should   │
│ be skipped.                                                  │
│                                                              │
│ I will now edit the `simplifyUDivInst` function to include   │
│ this additional check.                                       │
